Ok, so I've actually found the problem. Firefox *does* support classes, it *doesn't* support **fields** (variable definitions) in classes. This is where the problem is in the code (lines 72-82):

```javascript
		dataURLtoFile = function(dataurl, filename) {
			var arr = dataurl.split(','),
				mime = arr[0].match(/:(.*?);/)[1],
				bstr = atob(arr[1]),
				n = bstr.length,
				u8arr = new Uint8Array(n);
			while (n--) {
				u8arr[n] = bstr.charCodeAt(n);
			}
			return new File([u8arr], filename, { type: mime });
		};
```

This is a field/variable. It needs to be converted into a regular function: `dataURLtoFile(dataurl, filename) {`.
